        rotary - the Rotary arm mechanism
        extension - the extension arm subsystem
        manipulator - the manipulator subsystem

      • autonCommandGenerator

        public AutonCommand autonCommandGenerator​(com.pathplanner.lib.PathPlannerTrajectory trajectory)
        Generates an AutonCommand object from a PathPlannerTrajectory trajectory. Trajectory's can be loaded from path planner with PathPlanner.loadPath(nameOfYourTrajectory, accelerationAndVelocityConstraints). For an example see generate3MeterDrive(). Trajectory's can be made from a list of points by passing in a list of positions: The first Translation2d is a translation that the bot should follow The second parameter is a Rotation2d rotation, the rotation dictates the Spline that is made, which is basically the rotation of the plane that intersects the wheels when the bot gets to a position
        Parameters:
        trajectory - the trajectory from PathPlanner to follow
        Returns:
        an AutonCommand object that contains an auton path to run as well as the start and end points
        See Also:
        An explanation on holonomic rotation vs heading. The third parameter is another Rotation2d rotation, this rotation does not affect the path that the bot takes and instead is a holonomic rotation, that dictates the direction that the chassis will face.
